--- !u!114 &1267645774
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1267645772}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 48fdfcc8a67199e4aa51c8e7b7b14715, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::WitcherRightVersion.Dialogue.DialogueInteractable
  displayName: Orten
  interactionPrompt: Confront
  startNodeId: start
  returnToElderNodeId: 
  completedQuestNodeId: 
  dialogueNodes:
  - Id: start
    SpeakerName: Orten
    Body: You call it a lie because you arrived after the blood dried. I call it
      surgery. A village cannot live while staring at its own wound.
    Choices:
    - Text: Your surgery made a curse.
      NextNodeId: accuse
      FlagToSet: OrtenConfronted
      QuestAction: orten_confronted
      ClosesDialogue: 0
    - Text: Maybe the lie saved them.
      NextNodeId: agree
      FlagToSet: MayorSupported
      QuestAction: 
      ClosesDialogue: 0
    - Text: I will break the mirror.
      NextNodeId: sacrifice
      FlagToSet: MirrorShardsDestroyed
      QuestAction: mirror_shards_destroyed
      ClosesDialogue: 0
    - Text: Leave.
      NextNodeId: 
      FlagToSet: 
      QuestAction: 
      ClosesDialogue: 1
  - Id: accuse
    SpeakerName: Orten
    Body: Then bring a better ending, witcher. Truth, comfort, or fire. The mirror
      only obeys a hand that has chosen.
    Choices:
    - Text: I have chosen enough.
      NextNodeId: 
      FlagToSet: 
      QuestAction: 
      ClosesDialogue: 1
  - Id: agree
    SpeakerName: Orten
    Body: A practical monster hunter. Voytsekh would have liked you before fear taught
      him manners.
    Choices:
    - Text: This version survives.
      NextNodeId: 
      FlagToSet: 
      QuestAction: 
      ClosesDialogue: 1
  - Id: sacrifice
    SpeakerName: Orten
    Body: Break it, then. But when the curse leaves, it will take what it still owns.
    Choices:
    - Text: Better a cruel end than an endless rot.
      NextNodeId: 
      FlagToSet: OrtenDiaryFound
      QuestAction: orten_diary_found
      ClosesDialogue: 1
